dismissalComment.html: well bowled again, and it earns a run out! Full and fast at leg stump, jabbed back to the bowler. Prasanna thought it would bounce over Jordan and had already raced off for the run and it was a simple job for the bowler to remove the bails

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root lbw b Prasanna 80 (99b 5x4 0x6 142m) SR: 80.8

dismissalComment.html: and now he's given! Going for the reverse sweep, misses the full delivery, and Rod Tucker is quick to say that's out. England have their review so Root reckons he may as well use it, but that looks fairly straight. Only an edge would save him, but it wasn't an instant review from Root. And it's hitting middle half-way up. That ends a fine series for Root, one of the England players who can hold their head high

dismissalText.commentary: Alastair Cook c Jayawardene b Lakmal 32 (49b 3x4 1x6 47m) SR: 65.3

dismissalComment.html: full length sliding across the off stump, Cook drives at it and edges, well taken at slip! Jayawardene diving low to his left takes the catch but they will check upstairs. Absolutely no question of a clean catch, very well held and Cook, having had several near-misses, finally has to go with another stroke that he played without moving his feet, back goes the England captain without a big score once more

dismissalText.commentary: James Taylor c Sangakkara b Lakmal 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: back of a length at the body, it bounces a little and Taylor tries to fend it off, taken by Sangakkara and it's given out! England in disarray now. A little bounce made it really uncomfortable for Taylor who tried to ride the delivery down the leg side but it got a bit big on him and he clearly gloves it behind, Rod Tucker gave it out straight away

dismissalText.commentary: James Tredwell st Sangakkara b Jayawardene 17 (21b 1x4 1x6 20m) SR: 80.95

dismissalComment.html: there it is! The pair combine. Mahela and Kumar. Tredwell charges down the pitch, misses by a mile and Sangakkara completes the simple stumping. Plenty of smiles and hugs from the Sri Lanka players.

headshotImage.caption: Seekkuge Prasanna player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Seekkuge Prasanna player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: James Tredwell st Sangakkara b Jayawardene 17 (21b 1x4 1x6 20m) SR: 80.95

commentTextItems.html: there it is! The pair combine. Mahela and Kumar. Tredwell charges down the pitch, misses by a mile and Sangakkara completes the simple stumping. Plenty of smiles and hugs from the Sri Lanka players.

commentPostTextItems.html: So Sri Lanka have won by 87 runs and take the series 5-2. Sangakkara and Jayawardene leading the team off, they wave to the masses in the stands. Dilshan not far behind them. What a great atmosphere. Cook shakes Jayawardene's hand, then Sangakkara's. They are taking the moment with a walk around the ground, the crowd are loving it. Dilshan is there, too. The standing ovation continues as the pair walk around the outfield. For Mahela, this is it in Sri Lanka. That's certain. Sangakkara, we don't quite know yet.
Manish: "Vamsi Sidda could also have wondered about how romantic would it be if Sri Lanka won the World Cup next Year! :P"

Cook: "It was too many runs for us to chase. It's been a tough tour but people have come through personally. Root has been outstanding, also Woakes and Jordan. We've worked incredibly hard, left everything on the pitch but haven't been good enough. It's great to see so many celebrate Kumar and Mahela and I'd like to thank our fans as well."

Man of the Match - Dilshan: "It was a great to finish with the hundred. I'm really happy with the all-round performance in this series. All the things are clicking ahead of the World Cup with the youngsters, everyone is doing well. I will really miss them [Kumar and Mahela] but it's another 10-15 matches until they finish. My body is feeling good, I can see after the World Cup where I'll end up." Dilshan is also Man of the Series

Mathews: "[Dilshan] The older he gets the fast he gets. Really exciting about the World Cup, but have to enjoy this first then get on the plane tomorrow. I want to say a big thank you to all the people who turned up to support us. It will be a sad day after the services they [Kumar and Mahela] have rendered and the guidance they have given."

And up come Mahela and Kumar. Mahela: "Thank you very much, it's been a long time coming. Thanks to my parents and friends and to all the support. It's important we have the support. It was a great series. It's sad and emotional but winning his fun."
The trophy is handed to Mathews and that just about wraps things up for us today. Sri Lanka have played some very fine cricket. England less so, although a few players showed promise.

Sri Lanka now head to New Zealand, England come home for Christmas. England will name their World Cup squad on Saturday and they then leave for Australia, and the tri-series, on January 7. We'll have coverage of all that for you, but the next cricket is in just a few hours with the second Australia-India Test and then South Africa-West Indies starts tomorrow. For now, though, from Andrew McGlashan and Alex Winter it's goodbye and thanks for joining us.

dismissalComment.html: well bowled again, and it earns a run out! Full and fast at leg stump, jabbed back to the bowler. Prasanna thought it would bounce over Jordan and had already raced off for the run and it was a simple job for the bowler to remove the bails

dismissalText.commentary: Alastair Cook c Jayawardene b Lakmal 32 (49b 3x4 1x6 47m) SR: 65.3

dismissalComment.html: full length sliding across the off stump, Cook drives at it and edges, well taken at slip! Jayawardene diving low to his left takes the catch but they will check upstairs. Absolutely no question of a clean catch, very well held and Cook, having had several near-misses, finally has to go with another stroke that he played without moving his feet, back goes the England captain without a big score once more

dismissalText.commentary: Moeen Ali b Dilshan 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: goes back, this skids on, Moeen cuts, misses and is bowled! Dilshan strikes first up yet again and perhaps there most dangerous player is back in the shed first ball. No turn at all and Moeen has misjudged this completely and lost his off stump

headshotImage.caption: Seekkuge Prasanna player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Seekkuge Prasanna player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Hales c Prasanna b Dilshan 7 (15b 0x4 0x6 17m) SR: 46.66

dismissalComment.html: down the track smashing high into the sky but doesn't get enough of it and finds long-on! Hales got it off the bottom of the bat, it went very high but a good five yards short of the boundary and it was solidly taken, England in trouble

headshotImage.caption: Seekkuge Prasanna player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Seekkuge Prasanna player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root lbw b Prasanna 80 (99b 5x4 0x6 142m) SR: 80.8

dismissalComment.html: and now he's given! Going for the reverse sweep, misses the full delivery, and Rod Tucker is quick to say that's out. England have their review so Root reckons he may as well use it, but that looks fairly straight. Only an edge would save him, but it wasn't an instant review from Root. And it's hitting middle half-way up. That ends a fine series for Root, one of the England players who can hold their head high

headshotImage.caption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: James Taylor c Sangakkara b Lakmal 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: back of a length at the body, it bounces a little and Taylor tries to fend it off, taken by Sangakkara and it's given out! England in disarray now. A little bounce made it really uncomfortable for Taylor who tried to ride the delivery down the leg side but it got a bit big on him and he clearly gloves it behind, Rod Tucker gave it out straight away

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan lbw b Dilshan 4 (14b 0x4 0x6 25m) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: England's slide continues! Massive appeal for lbw as Morgan sweeps a full delivery, given not out on the field and they call for the review. Looks pretty straight, is there an bottom edge? Decided there's no edge and that's crashing into middle and leg. Morgan has to go

dismissalComment.html: picked him out! Just as Buttler was getting going. Tried to clear the off side but the bat just turned in his hand and the ball sliced in the air to deep cover

headshotImage.longCaption: Dilruwan Perera player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Woakes b MDK Perera 34 (37b 2x4 0x6 48m) SR: 91.89

dismissalComment.html: dance down the pitch, the bowler saw him, fired it right in the blockhole and clean him up! Woakes has played pretty well but now forced to try and raise the tempo, comes down and aims a drive into the off side, the quicker ball beat him and knocked out leg stump
